# =============================================================================
# MADCounter .gitignore
# =============================================================================
#
# WHY THIS FILE EXISTS:
# Git tracks every file in your project by default.
# Some files should NEVER be in a git repository:
#
#   Compiled binaries: Platform-specific, large, change every compile.
#                      Recipients should compile from source themselves.
#
#   OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db): Created automatically by OS,
#                      meaningless to others, just noise.
#
#   Editor swap files (.swp, *~): Created by vim/emacs during editing,
#                      should never be shared.
#
#   Temporary output files: Files created during testing.
#
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Compiled binary
# The `madcounter` binary is compiled from MADCounter.c.
# Everyone cloning the repo should compile it themselves with: make
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
madcounter

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Object files (produced when compiling with -c flag)
# Not relevant here since MADCounter.c is a single-file project,
# but good practice to include.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.o
*.a
*.so
*.dylib

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# macOS system files
# .DS_Store = macOS Finder metadata (folder icons, window sizes)
# These are machine-specific and useless to others.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
Icon?

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Linux system files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*~

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Windows system files (in case anyone uses WSL)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Thumbs.db
ehthumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editor swap/backup files
# vim creates .swp files while editing (crash recovery)
# emacs creates # and ~ files
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.swp
*.swo
*~
\#*\#
.\#*

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build directories
# If you ever add a src/ layout, compiled output goes here
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
dist/
build/
out/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Test output files
# Don't commit test outputs â€” graders run tests themselves
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
output*.txt
test_output*.txt
/tmp/

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Valgrind output (memory leak detector)
# valgrind --log-file=vglog.txt ./madcounter...
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
vgcore.*
vglog.txt
